A: Here is the code you need:
public void checkCredentials() {
    try {
        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(new File("accounts.txt")));
        String line;
        String username = "";
        String password = "";
        while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
            if (line.startsWith("usrnm:")) {
                username = line.substring(6); // get the part after "usrnm:"
            } else if (line.startsWith("pswrd:")) {
                password = line.substring(6); // get the part after "pswrd:"
            }
        }
        br.close();
        System.out.println("username: " + username);
        System.out.println("password: " + password);
    } catch (Exception ex) {
        ex.printStackTrace();
    }
}

This code reads the file line by line. If a line starts with "usrnm:", it sets the username variable to the part of the line after "usrnm:". If a line starts with "pswrd:", it sets the password variable to the part of the line after "pswrd:". After reading the file, it prints the username and password.

